Azory Gwanda is a Tanzanian investigative journalist known for exposing corruption and criminal activities. In 2017, he mysteriously disappeared, highlighting the serious risks journalists face when revealing sensitive information in environments with limited press freedom.

Protecting data and communications is vital for journalists like Azory to stay safe. Secure, encrypted messaging and offline communication tools help prevent interception and tracking by hostile parties, reducing the risk of harm or disappearance. Understanding terms like investigative journalism, digital privacy, data encryption, offline security, and press freedom can provide deeper insight into the importance of protecting sensitive information.